Document: ProceduralSkyMaterial
Path: godot/classes/class_proceduralskymaterial.rst
Summary: Defines a sky material that procedurally generates a sky based on physical parameters.

ProceduralSkyMaterial

Inherits: SkyMaterial < Material < Resource < RefCounted

A sky material that procedurally generates a sky based on physical parameters. This is useful for creating realistic or stylized skies without needing to use a skybox texture.

Properties:
sun_angle_max (float): The maximum angle of the sun disk. Larger values make the sun disk appear larger. Default: 0.05
sun_disc (bool): Whether to draw the sun disc. Default: true
ground_color (Color): The color of the ground. Default: Color(0.3, 0.4, 0.5, 1)
sky_color (Color): The color of the sky at the zenith. Default: Color(0.4, 0.6, 0.8, 1)
horizon_color (Color): The color of the horizon. Default: Color(0.6, 0.7, 0.8, 1)
scatter_horizon_factor (float): Controls how much the horizon color scatters. Higher values make the horizon more prominent. Default: 1.0
scatter_horizon_power (float): Controls the falloff of the horizon scattering. Higher values create a sharper transition. Default: 1.0
rayleigh_coefficient (Color): The Rayleigh scattering coefficient. This affects the blue color of the sky. Default: Color(0.001, 0.001, 0.001, 1)
mie_coefficient (Color): The Mie scattering coefficient. This affects the white haze and sun disk color. Default: Color(0.001, 0.001, 0.001, 1)
mie_direction (float): The direction of Mie scattering. Controls the forward/backward scattering of light. Default: 0.76
mie_azimuth (float): The azimuth of Mie scattering. Default: 0.0
mie_elevation (float): The elevation of Mie scattering. Default: 0.0
mie_scale (float): The scale of Mie scattering. Default: 0.001
luminance_multiplier (float): Multiplies the sky's luminance. Default: 1.0
energy_multiplier (float): Multiplies the sky's energy. Default: 1.0
