Document: ProceduralSkyMaterial
Path: godot/classes/class_proceduralskymaterial.rst
Summary: Describes the properties of the ProceduralSkyMaterial class, including brightness, ground and sky colors, and sun-related settings.

Property Descriptions
energy_multiplier (float): The sky's overall brightness multiplier. Higher values result in a brighter sky. Default: 1.0
Method: set_energy_multiplier(value: float)
Method: get_energy_multiplier() -> float

ground_bottom_color (Color): Color of the ground at the bottom. Blends with ground_horizon_color. Default: Color(0.2, 0.169, 0.133, 1)
Method: set_ground_bottom_color(value: Color)
Method: get_ground_bottom_color() -> Color

ground_curve (float): How quickly the ground_horizon_color fades into the ground_bottom_color. Default: 0.02
Method: set_ground_curve(value: float)
Method: get_ground_curve() -> float

ground_energy_multiplier (float): Multiplier for ground color. A higher value will make the ground brighter. Default: 1.0
Method: set_ground_energy_multiplier(value: float)
Method: get_ground_energy_multiplier() -> float

ground_horizon_color (Color): Color of the ground at the horizon. Blends with ground_bottom_color. Default: Color(0.6463, 0.6558, 0.6708, 1)
Method: set_ground_horizon_color(value: Color)
Method: get_ground_horizon_color() -> Color

sky_cover (Texture2D): The sky cover texture to use. This texture must use an equirectangular projection. The texture's colors will be added to the existing sky color, and will be multiplied by sky_energy_multiplier and sky_cover_modulate. This is mainly suited to displaying stars at night, but it can also be used to display clouds at day or night (with a non-physically-accurate look).
Method: set_sky_cover(value: Texture2D)
Method: get_sky_cover() -> Texture2D

sky_cover_modulate (Color): The tint to apply to the sky_cover texture. This can be used to change the sky cover's colors or opacity independently of the sky energy, which is useful for day/night or weather transitions. Only effective if a texture is defined in sky_cover. Default: Color(1, 1, 1, 1)
Method: set_sky_cover_modulate(value: Color)
Method: get_sky_cover_modulate() -> Color

sky_curve (float): How quickly the sky_horizon_color fades into the sky_top_color. Default: 0.15
Method: set_sky_curve(value: float)
Method: get_sky_curve() -> float

sky_energy_multiplier (float): Multiplier for sky color. A higher value will make the sky brighter. Default: 1.0
Method: set_sky_energy_multiplier(value: float)
Method: get_sky_energy_multiplier() -> float

sky_horizon_color (Color): Color of the sky at the horizon. Blends with sky_top_color. Default: Color(0.6463, 0.6558, 0.6708, 1)
Method: set_sky_horizon_color(value: Color)
Method: get_sky_horizon_color() -> Color

sky_top_color (Color): Color of the sky at the top. Blends with sky_horizon_color. Default: Color(0.385, 0.454, 0.55, 1)
Method: set_sky_top_color(value: Color)
Method: get_sky_top_color() -> Color

sun_angle_max (float): Distance from center of sun where it fades out completely. Default: 30.0
Method: set_sun_angle_max(value: float)
Method: get_sun_angle_max() -> float

sun_curve (float): How quickly the sun fades away between the edge of the sun disk and sun_angle_max. Default: 0.15
Method: set_sun_curve(value: float)
Method: get_sun_curve() -> float

use_debanding (bool): If true, enables debanding. Debanding adds a small amount of noise which helps reduce banding that appears from the smooth changes in color in the sky. Default: true
Method: set_use_debanding(value: bool)
Method: get_use_debanding() -> bool